            Indeed, that is the precise intention of noble Lords in tabling their various amendments. I have not heard an argument about why there would not be merit in seven years' time in giving some flexibility and freedom to consider such issues to a successor Secretary of State&#x2014;or even the existing Secretary of State should she still be in post, which is highly unlikely.</p><p>
            If possible, can the Minister explain why this is the only deal on the table and why there is no merit in the cross-party views that have been expressed to allow a future Secretary of State to take into account all the relevant factors when considering a renewal of the exclusive licence for pool betting?
